    author:"Joseph Schumpeter (1942)",
    summary:"Entrepreneurs disrupt equilibrium through new combinations.",
    professionalDefinition:"Creative Destruction is the economic process by which entrepreneurs disrupt market equilibrium through new combinations — of products, methods, organisations, supply sources or markets — that destroy existing economic structures while simultaneously creating new ones of greater value (Schumpeter, 1942). It is the engine, not the disturbance, of capitalist economic change.",
