    summary:"Start with Why → How → What. People buy why, not what.",
    professionalDefinition:"The Golden Circle is a three-ring model of inspirational communication in which an organisation articulates its purpose ('Why'), distinctive process ('How'), and offerings ('What') in that order — from inside out — to engage the limbic brain where loyalty and decision-making reside (Sinek, 2009).",
    whoDeveloped:"Simon Sinek (b. 1973), British-American author and speaker, introduced the Golden Circle in his 2009 TED talk 'How Great Leaders Inspire Action' and the accompanying book Start With Why. The talk became one of TED's most-viewed videos of all time, with over 50 million views.",
