    whoDeveloped:"Geoffrey A. Moore (b. 1946), Silicon Valley consultant and author, identified the chasm phenomenon while consulting for tech companies in the late 1980s. The 1991 book Crossing the Chasm refined Rogers' diffusion curve with empirical observations from dozens of high-tech ventures that had succeeded with early adopters but stalled before the mainstream.",
