    professionalDefinition:"PESTLE is a structured environmental scan that examines six categories of macro-environmental forces — Political, Economic, Social, Technological, Legal and Environmental — that originate outside the firm but materially shape industry conditions, opportunities and risks (Aguilar, 1967, expanded over subsequent decades).",
    whoDeveloped:"Francis J. Aguilar of Harvard Business School introduced the original ETPS scan (Economic, Technical, Political, Social) in Scanning the Business Environment (1967). The acronym was extended progressively — to PEST, then PESTEL/PESTLE, adding Legal and Environmental — through the 1980s–2000s, with no single attributable author for the extensions.",
