    summary:"Customer profile (jobs, pains, gains) ↔ Value map (products, pain relievers, gain creators).",
    professionalDefinition:"The Value Proposition Canvas is a two-side visual tool for designing and testing fit between customer needs and product offerings. The right side maps the customer profile (jobs to be done, pains, gains); the left side maps the value proposition (products and services, pain relievers, gain creators); fit is achieved when left matches right (Osterwalder et al., 2014).",
    whoDeveloped:"Alexander Osterwalder (b. 1974) and Yves Pigneur (b. 1954), co-founders of Strategyzer, developed the canvas as a deeper companion to their earlier Business Model Canvas. The 2014 book Value Proposition Design (with Greg Bernarda and Alan Smith) made the framework standard in product and innovation work.",
