    num:"F23", title:"TAM-SAM-SOM Market Sizing", unit:3, slibrary:6, pedagogy:"Role Play",
    author:"Investor practice (1990s onward)",
    summary:"Total · Serviceable · Obtainable Market — three nested rings.",
    professionalDefinition:"TAM-SAM-SOM is a three-tier market-sizing convention used in venture investment: Total Addressable Market (the entire universe of potential demand), Serviceable Available Market (the portion reachable with the firm's current model and geography), and Serviceable Obtainable Market (the portion realistically winnable in 3–5 years given competition and resources) (industry practice).",
