    whenToUse:"In strategy review, especially in mature firms where strategy has degraded into a list of initiatives without integration; in board reviews; and in strategy education.",
    byWhom:"Strategy academics, executive teams, corporate strategy directors, family-business chairs, and consultants.",
    innovation:"Compared with mission-vision-values frameworks, the Diamond demands operational specificity (especially Staging and Economic Logic). Compared with Porter's generic strategies, it accommodates hybrid positions and explicitly addresses sequencing.",
    figureCaption:"A diamond shape with five vertices, each labelled with one element (Arenas, Vehicles, Differentiators, Staging, Economic Logic); a central element (the strategy itself) sits at the diamond's centre.",
