    whoDeveloped:"Andrew S. Grove (1936–2016), Intel CEO, developed the system in the 1970s as a refinement of Drucker's Management by Objectives, calling it iMBOs. John Doerr (b. 1951), Kleiner Perkins partner, learned OKRs at Intel and introduced them at Google in 1999, from where the framework spread to most major technology firms.",
