    innovation:"Compared with Porter's positioning view, Bhide's hustle frame recognises that for most early ventures, structural advantage is unavailable and speed is the only viable substitute. Compared with later 'lean' frameworks (Ries, 2011), Bhide pre-dated and anticipated the emphasis on cycle-time as the key metric.",
