    innovation:"Compared with Schumpeter's general theory of creative destruction (F1), Christensen specified the direction of disruption (low-end and new-market) and the mechanism (rational resource allocation defeating itself). Compared with Porter's positioning view, Christensen argued that strategic positioning could become the very source of vulnerability.",
