    professionalDefinition:"Pinchot's 10 Commandments are a set of behavioural prescriptions for the corporate intrapreneur — the person seeking to create new ventures inside a large organisation — that name the political and cultural obstacles distinct from independent entrepreneurship and prescribe the practices that overcome them (Pinchot, 1985).",
    whoDeveloped:"Gifford Pinchot III (b. 1942), American author and entrepreneur educator, coined the term 'intrapreneuring' in a 1978 essay co-authored with Elizabeth Pinchot, then formalised the 10 Commandments in Intrapreneuring (1985). The Pinchots later founded the Bainbridge Graduate Institute (now Pinchot University).",
