    author:"Vijay Govindarajan (2016)",
    summary:"Manage present · Selectively forget past · Create future — concurrently.",
    professionalDefinition:"The 3-Box Solution is a framework for sustaining corporate innovation that prescribes three concurrent activities — Box 1 (manage the present efficiently), Box 2 (selectively forget the practices and assumptions that no longer serve), and Box 3 (create the future through experimental ventures) — with deliberate balance across all three (Govindarajan, 2016).",
    whoDeveloped:"Vijay Govindarajan (b. 1949), Coxe Distinguished Professor at the Tuck School of Business, Dartmouth College, developed the framework over two decades of research with major corporations including IBM, GE, P&G and Hasbro, and presented it in The Three-Box Solution (2016).",
