    summary:"H1 core · H2 emerging · H3 future — pipeline management.",
    professionalDefinition:"The Three Horizons of Growth is a portfolio framework that classifies a firm's growth initiatives into three categories — Horizon 1 (extending and defending the core business), Horizon 2 (building emerging businesses with proven models that are scaling rapidly), and Horizon 3 (creating viable options for future businesses) — and prescribes concurrent investment across all three (Baghai, Coley & White, 1999).",
