    whoDeveloped:"Ichak Adizes (b. 1937), Israeli-American management consultant and founder of the Adizes Institute, developed the model through five decades of work with thousands of organisations across more than 70 countries. The framework was first published in How to Solve the Mismanagement Crisis (1979) and elaborated in Corporate Lifecycles (1988).",
    whyDeveloped:"Adizes observed that managerial advice that worked at one organisational phase often actively harmed firms at another phase. He sought a developmental framework that prescribed phase-appropriate interventions, treating organisations as having developmental tasks distinct from operational tasks.",
