    professionalDefinition:"A Capitalization Table (cap table) is the source-of-truth record of equity ownership in a company, listing each shareholder's holdings (common, preferred, options, warrants, convertible instruments) and updating with every funding event, option grant or equity transaction; it is the document founders, investors, lawyers and acquirers reference for ownership decisions (industry practice).",
