    author:"VC industry standard",
    summary:"Pre + Investment = Post. Investor's % = Investment ÷ Post.",
    professionalDefinition:"Pre-Money Valuation is the value assigned to a company before a financing round; Post-Money Valuation equals Pre-Money plus the new Investment amount; the investor's ownership percentage equals Investment divided by Post-Money — the most-confused but most-consequential calculation in early-stage finance, materially affected by where the option pool is created (in pre-money, founders dilute; in post-money, investors dilute) (VC industry standard).",
