    professionalDefinition:"SUCCESs is a six-attribute checklist for designing memorable messages, derived from analysis of why some ideas spread while others die: Simple (one core message), Unexpected (break a pattern to gain attention), Concrete (sensory specificity), Credible (with evidence or details), Emotional (felt, not just understood), and Stories (told as narrative rather than abstraction) (Heath & Heath, 2007).",
    whoDeveloped:"Chip Heath, professor at Stanford GSB, and Dan Heath, fellow at Duke's CASE centre, developed the framework in Made to Stick (2007). The book drew on decades of psychology, sociology, marketing and communication research synthesised through case studies of sticky and unsticky messages.",
