    professionalDefinition:"Power Posing is the practice of adopting expansive, open postures (e.g., arms raised, chest out, hands on hips) for two minutes before high-stakes events, on the basis of research suggesting the posture shifts both observer perception and self-perception, reducing cortisol and improving confidence-related performance — though the original neuroendocrine claims have been contested in subsequent replication studies (Cuddy et al., 2010; Carney & Cuddy retracted neuroendocrine claims, 2016).",
