    professionalDefinition:"The Risk-Reward Matrix is a 2×2 (or 5×5) grid plotting risks by Likelihood (probability of occurrence) and Impact (severity if occurred), used to prioritise which risks demand active mitigation, which can be accepted, and which require contingency planning — with each high-impact risk assigned an owner and a mitigation plan (general risk-management practice; ISO 31000).",
